Just adding one point. if you see a bub of smoke on the ground, hi thats a xakra trap <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149468><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/broodwar/popup/lurker.gif ><a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelendar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elendar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/02 9:05:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Recent mob change in The Grey</span><hr size=1> Anyone notice the worm traps move now?  Or at least some do.  So just avoiding them when running around won't always work, because they can roam into aggro range.  Just an FYI.<br>
